<para> The Single-Tier ODBC Drivers for Oracle conform to the common architectural perceptions of an ODBC driver -- a single component installed on a desktop, workstation, or application server machine that depends on additional database specific networking middleware (from the relevant database vendor) for local or remote database connectivity.</para><para>The <ulink url="OpenLink">OpenLink</ulink>  Single-Tier Drivers for Oracle are a Type A class driver developed using the Oracle OCI call level interface and assumes the pre installation of Oracle SQL*Net, Net8, Net9, or Net10 depending on your Oracle Server release.</para><para>These drivers are currently available for Oracle versions 7.x, 8.x, 9.x, 10.x and beyond.</para><para>  [[/images/aodbcst.gif|]]</para><para> /Oracle Single-Tier Architecture Diagram Image scaled down; Click to enlarge./</para><para> This driver is available for Windows, Linux, Unix(most popular flavours) and Mac OS X Operating systems.</para><para> </para></section></docbook>